Articles.Content: I have seen the space shuttle, Soyuz, constellation, Saturn V, SLS, and more on the forum, but I haven't come across any replicas of the Chinese rockets/orbiters. Does anyone have one? Post here if you do.
I have a jade rabbit mun lander and rover in my stock craft repository:

Hi , I try this today ! The CZ-E2 replica ! i find only few info's on it , this was a Chinese orbital carrier rocket. Designed to launch commercial communications satellites . It's first flight on 16 July 1990 !

Sure ppl can make smth better than that , but i want to try it !

If you want to try it : https://onedrive.live.com/redir?resid=B4FEC25180514B47!1114&authkey=!AGCMRBgzIaA7JJg&ithint=file%2ccraft

Mostly stock + 1 Kethane scanner part , 6 ProceduralFairings parts & 8 Firespitter struts !

Oh , Engineer part for fly info !
